(Contributor Dataset QA Guide) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(Purpose: verify seeded exam records before student release or model training.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Review steps) Tj
T*
(1. Enter your reviewer name before saving any decision.) Tj
T*
(2. Select the past exam year in Dataset QA.) Tj
T*
(3. Open the first Ready for QA record in the queue.) Tj
T*
(4. Compare the rendered question with the original exam or trusted source.) Tj
T*
(5. Check marks, topic, subtopic, answer type, and manual-review flag.) Tj
T*
(6. For auto-check questions, run the marker using the expected answer.) Tj
T*
(7. Read the worked solution and marking rubric for accuracy and clarity.) Tj
T*
(8. Save a decision: Approve, Needs Fix, Manual, or Reject.) Tj
T*
(9. Write a short reviewer note explaining what you checked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Status rules) Tj
T*
(Approve: question text, answer, solution, rubric, topic, and marker are correct.) Tj
T*
(Needs Fix: the record is useful but contains a correctable problem.) Tj
T*
(Manual: graph, proof, explanation, or non-machine-markable item needs human review.) Tj
T*
(Reject: the record is too wrong, duplicated, incomplete, or unsafe for the dataset.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
